cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.AR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the physical layer data transmissions and communication technologies such as LTE and 5G NR.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the Bit/Block Error Rate (BER/BLER) for various scenarios, which is a key concept in information theory.
- cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the PDCCH processing chain in LTE and 5G NR, which are communication technologies.
- cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the evolved Multimedia Broadcast Multicast Service (eMBMS), which is a technology that can be used for AR/VR applications.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the performance of the PDCCH in relation to the Physical Downlink Shared Channel (PDSCH), which is used for multimedia data transmissions.
